/*
here i am talking about variables
1.what is variable ?
-->I is a container to store data how we store things in boxes,bottles
2.Types of variables
--> INT FLOAT DOUBLE CHAR _BOOL
3.usage :
int → stores whole numbers, e.g., int age = 20;

float → stores decimal numbers, e.g., float pi = 3.14;

double → high-precision decimal numbers, e.g., double price = 99.99;

char → stores a single character, e.g., char grade = 'A';

_Bool → stores boolean, 0 (false) or 1 (true)
Tip: Always choose the type that fits your data to optimize memory!

*/

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int age = 21;
    char grade = 'A';
    float marks = 88.5;
    printf("Age: %d, Grade: %c, Marks: %.2f\n", age, grade, marks);
    return 0;
}







